The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Aug. 20: Housing Development Finance Corporation Ltd today raised Rs 4,300 crore from a QIP issue that comprised warrants along with non-convertible debentures. The issue price of Rs 275 per warrant will be received by the corporation on the pay-in date. HDFC issued 1,09,53,706 warrants.                             
	 Mumbai, Aug. 20: The Air India board today decided to reduce by 50 per cent the productivity-linked incentives or flying allowance payable to its employees. The reduction will be effective till an alternative formula for governing the productivity-linked incentive is put in place within three-months.                            
	 Calcutta, Aug. 20: Hindusthan National Glass and Industries is looking to acquire container glass manufacturing firms with a Rs 400-crore turnover in Africa, southeast and west Asian countries.                                                                                                                           
